Before presenting the aggregated results, we outline the
coding process for modeling the theoretical  structures and
the concepts developed in that process. Given the  limited
space, we represent only one of the smallest evidence models,
extracted from study S1 (see Fig.  2). The study assesses
various model quantization techniques  to overcome energy
limitations of wearable devices for respiratory classification.
Identifying the effects was straightforward as they mapped
to the dependent variables, which are clearly reported in the
study. Regarding the effect intensity, we extracted it directly
from the data reported in the study. We compute the average
improvement relative to the non-quantized baselines for each
effect and then determine the intensity based on the thresholds
shown in Fig. 3. For instance,  the effect intensity for “Infer-
ence energy consumption” was defined as {SP} since the
average relative improvement was 57.18%. The belief values

